Netflix Movie Recommendation System

This project focuses on analyzing Netflix movie data by cleaning the dataset and performing Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to uncover trends in movie genres, ratings, runtime, language distribution, and release years.

Project Workflow:

1. Data Cleaning
Handled missing values and inconsistencies.
Converted data types for better analysis.
Removed duplicates and standardized formats.

2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Top Genre by IMDB Rating: Identified the highest-rated genre among English-language movies.
Average Runtime of Hindi Movies: Calculated and analyzed the average runtime of movies shot in Hindi.
Genre Distribution: Counted and visualized all unique genres in the dataset.
Most Used Languages: Found the top 3 most frequently used languages in movies.
Year with Most Movie Releases: Determined which year had the highest number of movie releases and visualized the trend.
Year with the Greatest Total Runtime: Identified the year in which movies had the highest combined runtime.

Technologies Used:
Python: Data analysis and visualization
Pandas & NumPy: Data manipulation and cleaning
Matplotlib & Seaborn: Data visualization
